HEADWORD: Tetrazole
<hw>Tet*raz"ole</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Tetrazo-</ets> + <ets>-ole</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Org.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A crystalline acid substance, <chform>CH2N4</chform>,
which may be regarded as pyrrol in which nitrogen atoms replace three
<chform>CH</chform> groups; also, any of various derivatives of the
same.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

